    <div class="faq-accordion-list">
        <details>
            <summary>
                <h3>What should I do if I encounter a bug?</h3>
                <span class="faq-toggle-icon"></span>
            </summary>
            <div class="faq-content">
                <p>We’ve built Volo to be as reliable as possible, but if you do find a bug, please let us know. You can report any issues directly on our <a href="https://github.com/thisisrogerflanagan/volo-releases/issues/new?template=bug_report.yml" target="_blank">GitHub repository</a> or email us at thisisrogerflanagan@gmail.com.</p>
            </div>
        </details>

        <details>
            <summary>
                <h3>What makes Volo different from other screensavers?</h3>
                <span class="faq-toggle-icon"></span>
            </summary>
            <div class="faq-content">
                <p>Volo is a high-fidelity mechanical split-flap screensaver that prioritizes physical realism and tactile charm. Unlike static clocks, Volo utilizes "Vesta-Grade" physics and realistic 3D lighting to create an atmosphere that feels like a piece of crafted furniture for your modern workspace.</p>
            </div>
        </details>

        <details>
            <summary>
                <h3>How do I install the Volo screensaver on Mac?</h3>
                <span class="faq-toggle-icon"></span>
            </summary>
            <div class="faq-content">
                <p>After purchase, download the .dmg file and open it. Drag Volo to your Applications folder. Once launched, you can run Volo as a background agent or a standard application. To set it as your actual system screensaver, follow the instructions in the "Settings" panel within the app.</p>
            </div>
        </details>

        <details>
            <summary>
                <h3>Which macOS versions and Macs are supported?</h3>
                <span class="faq-toggle-icon"></span>
            </summary>
            <div class="faq-content">
                <p>Volo is designed exclusively for macOS and supports all modern Macs, including Intel and Apple Silicon (M1, M2, M3) chips. We recommend running macOS Monterey (12.0) or later for the best performance and integration.</p>
            </div>
        </details>

        <details>
            <summary>
                <h3>Does Volo cause screen burn-in on OLED displays?</h3>
                <span class="faq-toggle-icon"></span>
            </summary>
            <div class="faq-content">
                <p>Volo features built-in OLED Health Protection. This includes subtle pixel-jitter technology and intelligent auto-dimming to prevent static elements from remaining on your screen for too long, ensuring your high-end display remains safe and vibrant.</p>
            </div>
        </details>
    </div>

    <footer class="faq-help-footer">
        <h2>Have more questions?</h2>
        <p>If you have any additional questions, do not hesitate to <a href="mailto:thisisrogerflanagan@gmail.com" class="faq-contact-link">contact us</a>.</p>
